727980f-c.text:
Shore Boulevard, east side, between 21st Road (left), and 2lst Drive (right) showing the A. D. Ditmar's house, formerly shingled, but now stuccoed. This house is on the site of the Daniel Mawrence house which was erected in 1719. In 1852 Dr. Dow
Ditmars was the occupant.
February 9, 1932
P. L. Sperr
(2), (3)
The same,showing another view of the same house at an earlier date.
March, 1923
Eugene L. Arbruster Collection
